{"word":"κομπέω","slug":"κομπέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κομπέω</b></el> <el>(κομπέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κόμπος'><el>κόμπος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to ring, clash</i>, <el>κόμπει χαλκός</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, like <el>κομπάζω</el>, <i>to speak big, boast, brag, vaunt</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>κ. μῦθον</el> <i>to speak a boastful</i> speech, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to boast of</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <i>to be boasted of</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}